title: Noor Ahmed of PPPP wins PS-47 election
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 9 (APP): Candidate of Pakistan Peoples Party Parliamentarians (PPPP) Noor Ahmed Bhurgri has won the Sindh Assembly election from PS-47 Mirpur Khas-III constituency by securing 56,522 votes.
According to the unofficial result issued by the Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up was an independent candidate Faisal Kachelo who bagged 17,420 votes.
Overall votersâ€™ turn-out remained 45.91 per cent in the constituency.
